        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36007",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi, Marcin.\r\n\r\nDo you mean you find mail returns back when some error is happened?\r\nOr, you find [from] address is changed on your mailer?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-14T04:59:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-14T04:59:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36008",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mgil",
                        "name": "mgil",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Gil",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Satoru,\r\n\r\nI mean that e-mail is sent from \"returns@email.com\" instead of \"sender@email.com\".\r\nI understand that e-mail should be sent from \"sender@email.com\" with Return-Path header set to \"returns@email.com\" - in case of error.\r\nDo I understand incorrectly?\r\n\r\nCheers,\r\nMarcin\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mgil",
                        "name": "mgil",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Gil",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-14T05:06:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-14T05:06:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36016",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I change code in SVN r18988 (trunk), 18989 (1.9 branch) .\r\n\r\nYou are correct, Marcin.\r\nFor your purpose, getReturnPath() should be replaced with getFrom().\r\n\r\nAnd I have a sadly information I must notice you :-(\r\nAs it is pointed out in ZF-7008, setReturnPath can not work fine now.\r\n\r\nThe function is under consideration how to fix.\r\n\r\n ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-15T05:37:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-15T05:37:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41750",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=luenne",
                        "name": "luenne",
                        "displayName": "Janis L\u00fcnne",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Satoru, hi Marcin,\r\n\r\nunfortunately this is broken now.\r\nThe Return-Path has to be used as MAIL FROM: in the SMTP transport.\r\nSo please undo your replacement of getReturnPath() with getFrom(), because it was working correctly before.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nJanis",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=luenne",
                        "name": "luenne",
                        "displayName": "Janis L\u00fcnne",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T05:46:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T05:46:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41751",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please present some code to reproduce, and describe the problem with that code. Thanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T05:52:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T05:52:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41769",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=luenne",
                        "name": "luenne",
                        "displayName": "Janis L\u00fcnne",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Mail_Transport_Smtp, line 203:\r\nwas (correct):\r\n$this->_connection->mail($this->_mail->getReturnPath());\r\nis now (incorrect):\r\n$this->_connection->mail($this->_mail->getFrom());\r\n\r\nThis results in always using the \"Body-From\" (From:-Header), as \"Envelope-From\" (\"MAIL FROM:\" SMTP command) and removes the possibility to use different Envelope-From and Body-From Addresses.\r\n\r\nSee RFC 2821 and http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bounce_address for reference.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=luenne",
                        "name": "luenne",
                        "displayName": "Janis L\u00fcnne",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-28T07:51:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-28T07:51:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41770",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ouch. Will fix tonight.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-28T07:54:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-28T07:54:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41921",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=swentz",
                        "name": "swentz",
                        "displayName": "Stephan Wentz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "*bump*\r\n\r\nIt's still not fixed in trunk - and it breaks our mail code ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=swentz",
                        "name": "swentz",
                        "displayName": "Stephan Wentz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-08-09T03:59:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-08-09T03:59:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42852",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "ZF-8988 was opened because this was not actually a bug and the \"solution\" broke Zend_Mail to not be compliant with the RFC with the SMTP transport.\r\n\r\nClosing this issue to avoid confusion -- see ZF-8988 for the fix.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-06T02:46:54.000+0000",
